      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Look at the News</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joanne Rubin letter wonders if young teens who reportedly have oral sex were influenced by Pres Clinton-Monica Lewinsky scandal</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In regard to the article about middle schoolers having oral sex (''The Face of Teenage Sex Grows Younger,'' April 2): Assuming that the surveys cited were accurate, I wonder if teens were being influenced by the daily coverage of President Clinton's impeachment proceedings, and all of the Monica Lewinsky coverage. If so, then the news media needs to face up to its responsibilities regarding sensationalism.</p>
        <p>JOANNE RUBIN  Hastings-on-Hudson, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
